<statement>
<p>
A population of bacteria is growing according to the equation <m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1400}{e}^{{{0.11}{t}}}</m>.  Estimate when the population will exceed 1926.</p>
<p>
<em>t</em>= <fillin characters="20" /> Â  </p>
<p>
Give your answer accurate to one decimal place.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>2.8997552432247</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1400}{e}^{{{0.11}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{1926}={1400}{e}^{{{0.11}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{1926}}{{1400}}={e}^{{{0.11}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{\ln{{\left(\frac{{1926}}{{1400}}\right)}}}={0.11}{t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{\ln{{\left(\frac{{1926}}{{1400}}\right)}}}}{{0.11}}={t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{t}={2.8997552432247}</m></p>
</solution>
